The Supplier SHALL supply precast concrete plinths (sokkelplaten) for use at the base of sandwich panel facades:

Product type: {{plinthType}}
Height: {{height}} mm
Thickness: {{thickness}} mm
Lengths: {{length}}
Concrete class: min {{concCl}}
Exposure class: min {{expCl}}
Reinforcement: {{rebar}}

Exterior finish: {{extFin}}
Interior finish: {{intFin}}
Colour/aggregate: {{colour}}

Anchors: {{anchors}}

Total quantity: {{qty}} pieces / {{totalLength}} m1

The Supplier SHALL:
- Manufacture plinths in accordance with the project drawings and this specification
- Ensure dimensional tolerances comply with EN 14992
- Provide cast-in anchor inserts at positions shown on drawings
- Ensure exterior face finish matches or is compatible with the adjacent sandwich panels
- Confirm maximum transportable piece length
- Confirm weight per piece

Confirm: concrete class, exposure class, fire classification, DoP/CE, weight/m1, maximum piece dimensions.

STM reserves the right to reject non-compliant alternatives.

The Supplier SHALL supply all cast-in items and accessories required for a complete plinth installation:

- Cast-in anchor inserts: {{anchorType}}, qty per piece: {{anchorQty}}
- Lifting anchors: included, type per Supplier's standard
- Grout pockets / levelling provisions: {{groutPocket}}
- Sealing strip / EPDM at base: {{sealingStrip}}

All cast-in items shall be supplied in stainless steel A4 or hot-dip galvanised unless specified otherwise.

The Supplier SHALL confirm:
- Anchor load capacity (tension and shear per anchor)
- Compatibility with steel substructure connection
- Installation instructions and setting-out templates
